LogFile.FinalText: A pet is found in many homes, and most people prefer a dog or a cat. So far, the soft puppy 'beats' the cute kitten in the race of being the most popular pet in Denmark. While the loyalty of the dog explains its popularity, the numerous car owners love the cat's independence. The general cat owner finds that a dog is too dependent and too dirty, whereas many dog owners see cats as lazy and impersonal. Many pet owners choose a pet that reflects their own personality. When the big, strong man buys a big, strong dog, the features of the dog reflect the dog owner's ego. In contrast, the feminine woman often prefers the pretty, elegant cat. Usually, cats and dogs get along without problems if they are used to each other. Often the dog owers and the cat owners fight more than the dogs and the cats themselves.
